I am disappointed to have to write this review. I visited this location while visiting NYC just before heading to visit the Statue of Liberty. In need of a caffeine fix, I thought it would be an excellent time to use the reward I had been saving for a couple of weeks.  I ordered an iced venti soy caramel macchiato. The only modification I requested was soy milk, so I didn't get complicated. After quite some time I finally had my drink called out to me. It was in a grande cup, so I knew something was not exactly right. When I grabbed the drink I noticed it had been rung up as a grande caramel macchiato sub caramel syrup. If anyone has ever had this beverage, they would know that caramel syrup is inappropriate-it should be vanilla. I politely explained that this was not the drink I ordered and told him what it was supposed to be. I immediately caught attitude and he rolled his eyes only to then tell me "well, they charged you for a grande". As an ex Starbucks partner myself, I immediately recognized that he was insinuating that I was trying to lie my way into a more expensive beverage (he did not acknowledge the caramel syrup issue). I told him it was a reward so the size didn't matter, it was free anyway. He then proceeded to stare at me until I had to overtly ask "Do you not believe me?" to which he scoffed and grabbed the drink back from me.  The drink I received was not appropriately remade as they are supposed to do, but rather dumped into a larger cup and added more ice and milk. I am sure the drink still had the wrong syrup because it tasted nothing like a caramel macchiato should, and I doubt it was made with soy milk. I was extremely offended that I was treated this way for no apparent reason and disappointed I wasted my earned reward on this beverage. Because of our ticket reservation I had no more time to waste at this establishment and did not even finish half of the drink before throwing it in the trash. I love Starbucks, but would warn anyone about this particular establishment.
